{
  "texts": [
    "Model order reduction encodingIndependent of the NN architecture, learning can be aided by applying the NN to a lower-dimensional space that is able to capture the data.",
    "For complex problems, mappings e to low-dimensional spaces (also referred to as latent space or latent vector) h can be identified with model order reduction techniques.",
    "Thus, in the case of simulation substitution, a low-dimensional encoding h λ = e(λ) of λ (sampled on all sample points x) is identified.",
    "This is provided as input to a NN to predict the solution field h u in a reduced latent space.",
    "The full solution field u (on all sample points x) is obtained in a decoding d = e -1 step."
  ]
}